  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Despite multiple credibility factors where achieved levels fall below required levels, the assurance level is declared High and the decision is Accepted — triggering COMPOUND-03 (assurance-level overstatement with Critical weakener W-AR-02 active).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim",
