    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and the availability of PIV validation data provide sufficient credibility to support regulatory submission. The assurance level is declared High based on the breadth of the 13-factor assessment and the quantitative uncertainty propagation performed. Gaps in discretization error, model form, and numerical solver error are acknowledged but judged acceptable given the conservative clinical threshold applied. Decision: Accepted with High assurance.",
